<p><placeName>Mouth of Brasos</placeName> <date when="1834-09-03">3d Septemr. 1834</date></p>
<p>Dear Sir.</p>

<p>I enclose for your perusal and the satisfaction of <persName>Mrs. Perry</persName> the
last letter that I have recd from our friend <persName>Col Austin</persName>. I wrote to
him from <placeName>Orleans </placeName>and further authorized him to draw on <persName>Beers,
St John and Co</persName> for <hi rend="italic">1,000$ </hi>which will last him until we can hear
further from him.</p>

<p>I leave here in the steam boat for <placeName>Columbia</placeName>. If I had made my
journey by Land should have done myself the pleasure of calling on
you.   I am very anxious to get home and am with esteem yr friend</p>

<p><persName>Samuel M Williams  </persName>  [Rubric]</p>

<p>[Addressed:] <persName>Mr. James F Perry </persName>  At <placeName>home</placeName></p>


        </div1>
